RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 77. Maiden Claiming Purse 19500. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $40,000 (Registered Florida Breds Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: VIDIANO raced off the pace up the backstretch, came around the turn in the three path, began a bid in upper stretch and gained ground late quickly to pull clear. CITY OF CLOUDS dueled on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, raced in the three path around the bend and continued to battle in the stretch but was caught late. WALT WHITMAN (IRE) trailed the field up the backstretch, raced in the four path around the turn and gained ground quickly in the final furlong. CRUISING DEREK dueled between horses up the backstretch, navigated the turn from the two path and kept on to the finish. FALK dueled on the inside through the early going, continued to battle while saving ground around the turn and in upper stretch and weakened in the final strides. CATALINA EXPRESS raced in the middle of the pack through the opening stages, came around the bend in the two path and was outkicked in the lane.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: REASONABLY LOVELY hopped up leaving the gate and was blocked, saved ground around the first turn, settled off the pace on the inside for the run up the backstretch, came around the far bend in the five path, began a bid passing the quarter pole and gained ground to pull clear late. INSATIABLE EVA bumped with the horse to her outside at the start, saved ground around the first turn, continued up the backstretch off the pace on the outside, navigated the far turn from the four path and improved position in the lane. MOVE TO ORDER trailed the field on the inside around the first turn and up the backstretch, came around the far bend in the three path and improved position in the final furlong. ROYALE FLARE bumped soundly with an outside horse at the start, raced at the back of the pack in the two path for the opening half mile, swung out to the five path for the run around the far turn and never threatened. ZIPPY ZINNY bumped hard with an inside horse leaving the gate, raced in the two path early, settled in the middle of the pack on the inside for the run up the backstretch, continued around the second turn in the three path and faded from there. HIGH DONNA raced in the three path around the first turn, stalked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, led the way while saving ground around the far bend and tired in the stretch. AFTER NOON KISSES bumped with the horse to her inside at the break, recovered to lead the way while saving ground around the first turn and up the backstretch, dropped back while racing on the rail around the far turn and tired further in the lane. VALIANT MISTRESS chased the leader between horses through the opening half mile, raced in the two path around the far turn and faded in the stretch.
